# Context Engine UI Design Rules

When changing frontend UI:

1. Create or update `specs/<surface>/requirements.md` before coding.
2. Research shadcn components/blocks and write `specs/<surface>/component-research.md` before implementation.
3. Preserve existing user capabilities and backend API contracts.
4. Keep shadcn primitives in `frontend/components/ui/`.
5. Keep shared app components in `frontend/components/app/`.
6. Keep feature-specific API/hooks/types/components in `frontend/features/<feature>/`.
7. Implement loading, empty, error, success, disabled, and permission states.
8. Run Playwright verification and write `specs/<surface>/verification-report.md`.
9. Do not use one-off colour systems or bespoke component variants unless added to shared design tokens.
10. Do not hide primary persistent configuration inside temporary sheets/dialogs unless explicitly requested.
